## Benchmark Strategy

Reproducibility is mandatory. No milestone is considered met without a
recorded wrk output plus environment metadata stored under
`benchmark/results/<yyyy-mm-dd>-<stage>-<target>.md`.

### Canonical setup

```bash
# Warmup
wrk -t1 -c64 -d10s http://127.0.0.1:8080/plaintext

# Measurement (take median of 3)
wrk -t1 -c64  -d30s --latency http://127.0.0.1:8080/plaintext   # throughput
wrk -t1 -c1   -d30s --latency http://127.0.0.1:8080/plaintext   # latency floor
wrk -t4 -c256 -d30s --latency http://127.0.0.1:8080/plaintext   # multi-thread (Stage 2+)
```

All servers (flare and baselines) serve the **same** TFB plaintext response:

```
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: 13

Hello, World!
```

No gzip, no cookies, no logging. Keep-alive on. Apples-to-apples.

### Baseline targets per stage

| Stage | Primary target | Stretch target | Reference ceiling |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Go `net/http` (`GOMAXPROCS=1`) | Go `fasthttp` (`GOMAXPROCS=1`), nginx 1 worker | — |
| 2 | Rust `hyper` (N workers) | drogon (N threads), Rust `actix-web` | — |
| 3 | h2o | may_minihttp | **uWebSockets** (ceiling, never the target) |

### Benchmark sources

| Source | Why it matters |
|---|---|
| [TechEmpower Framework Benchmarks](https://www.techempower.com/benchmarks/) | Gold standard; reproducible Docker setups; every major framework measured |
| [the-benchmarker/web-frameworks](https://github.com/the-benchmarker/web-frameworks) | Single-repo wrk benchmarks for 100+ frameworks; easier local repro |
| [uWebSockets benchmarks](https://github.com/uNetworking/uWebSockets/tree/master/benchmarks) | Reproduce the ceiling |
| [fasthttp comparison](https://github.com/valyala/fasthttp#http-server-performance-comparison-with-nethttp) | fasthttp vs net/http reference |

