## Stage 1 delivery (in-flight on `main`, not yet tagged)

Everything below has landed locally via commits; the v0.3.0 tag waits
until the 1.10× Go `net/http` milestone gate is met and the 7-day
nightly-CI green requirement clears.

**Completed (commits `c981095` through `7588ac2`, 12 atomic commits):**

- Phase 1.1 — `epoll` / `kqueue` / `eventfd` / pipe FFI + `set_nonblocking`
  helper in `flare/net/`, 22 tests.
- Phase 1.2 — `flare.runtime.Reactor` (uniform API, kqueue/epoll dispatched
  at comptime), `Event` type, 20 tests + 200K-run fuzz.
- Phase 1.3 — `flare.runtime.TimerWheel` (hashed, 512 slots + overflow,
  O(1) schedule/cancel), 18 tests + 100K-run property test.
- Phase 1.4 — `ConnHandle` state machine in `flare/http/_server_reactor_impl.mojo`
  (read → parse → dispatch → write → keep-alive / close), 15 tests + 30K-run
  fuzz.
- Phase 1.5 — **hard replacement** of `HttpServer` with the reactor-backed
  implementation. Old `_handle_connection_buffered` and blocking I/O helpers
  deleted. Public API and all 93 `test_server.mojo` tests pass unchanged.
- Phase 1.6 — rigorous bench harness under `benchmark/` with pinned
  toolchain (`[feature.bench.dependencies]` in `pixi.toml`: go, nginx),
  pre-flight body-integrity check, 5-run medians with 3%-stdev gate, full
  `env.json` provenance. Four baselines (flare, go_nethttp, go_fasthttp,
  nginx).
- Phase 1.7 — perf pass: +16% on TFB plaintext via bulk-copy read loop,
  readable→writable collapse, redundant `reactor.modify` elision. Current
  standing: **121,807 req/s, 0.86× Go net/http**. Milestone gate (1.10×)
  not yet met; remaining levers enumerated in `bench_vs_baseline.md`.
- Phase 1.8 (partial) — lifecycle + shutdown tests (7 tests). Full 7-day
  nightly CI gate is calendar-gated, starts once commits reach main.

